    <div class="hero">
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Deploy Your Ride-Pooling System on GitHub</h2>
            <p>Learn how to host your TUK RidePool project using GitHub Pages for free</p>
            <a href="#setup" class="btn btn-primary">Get Started</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
        <div class="card">
            <h3>Why Use GitHub?</h3>
            <p>GitHub is a platform for version control and collaboration. It allows you to:</p>
            <ul style="margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
                <li>Store your code securely in the cloud</li>
                <li>Track changes to your project over time</li>
                <li>Collaborate with others on your code</li>
                <li>Host your website for free with GitHub Pages</li>
                <li>Showcase your projects to potential employers</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h2 class="section-title" id="setup">Step-by-Step GitHub Setup</h2>

        <div class="card">
            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">1</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Create a GitHub Account</h4>
                    <p>Go to <a href="https://github.com/" target="_blank">github.com</a> and sign up for a free account if you don't have one.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">2</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Create a New Repository</h4>
                    <p>Click on the "+" icon in the top right corner and select "New repository".</p>
                    <div class="tip">
                        <strong>Naming tip:</strong> Name your repository <code>tuk-ridepool</code> or similar. 
                        For GitHub Pages to work automatically, you could name it <code>yourusername.github.io</code> 
                        (replace "yourusername" with your actual GitHub username).
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">3</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Initialize with a README</h4>
                    <p>Check the box that says "Add a README file". This will help you get started.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">4</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Upload Your HTML File</h4>
                    <p>After creating the repository, click on "Add file" → "Upload files". Drag and drop your HTML file or select it from your device.</p>
                    <div class="code-block">
        # Alternatively, you can use Git commands:
        git init
        git add .
        git commit -m "First commit"
        git branch -M main
        git remote add origin https://github.com/yourusername/your-repo-name.git
        git push -u origin main
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">5</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Enable GitHub Pages</h4>
                    <p>Go to Settings → Pages → Select "main" branch as source → Click Save.</p>
                    <div class="tip">
                        Your site will be published at <code>https://yourusername.github.io/repository-name</code>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="step">
                <div class="step-number">6</div>
                <div class="step-content">
                    <h4>Wait for Deployment</h4>
                    <p>It might take a few minutes for your site to be available. Refresh the page after a few minutes.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="section-title">Your Ride-Pooling System Preview</h2>

        <div class="preview">
            <h3 style="text-align: center; color: var(--primary); margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">TUK RidePool Booking System</h3>
            
